snippet.textDisplay: At it started with kidney stones so I got prescribed hydrocodone aka Vicodins. Then I found out I have  arthritis in my back and I got prescribed oxycodone 30m 4x a day. I used to take almost 10 a day plus 4 20mg Adderall throughout the day. I was on a Rollercoaster that was about to crash!! I had an addiction for a little over 2 years. I got pregnant to baby #4. I call her my miracle baby bc we was done having kids, was on birth control but I found out I was almost 4 months pregnant to her. Long story short, you can't completely stop taking meds while already pregnant, you need to see a specialist who monitors you and the baby. But, soon after I had my healthy baby girl, my oldest brother passed away from cirosis (sp) to the liver. I knew I needed to stop or I'll be next! It was the craziness, most hardest thing I put my family through. I still cringe when I think about the way I used to stand like a crackhead- arms all twisted and back bend in an awkward way, with my neck bend to the side - dude, it was UGLY! Thank God I didn't get a heart attack bc I was out of control! The medicine literally was the only thing on my mind 24/7. I used to think "how can I ever go back and have a regular life after this" bc the withdrawals were SO BAD! I am living a clean and sober life now and it feels Ah-may-zing! I got the help I needed and I have been clean and sober for over 5 years!!
